  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6816 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6810 (-77.9B) and positive gamma at 6830 (+29.8B), dealers are caught in a critical squeeze zone where they must buy any dips toward 6810 and sell any rallies toward 6830, creating amplified volatility in this narrow 20-point range. The breakout regime with -144B total GEX means dealers are aggressively short gamma and will accelerate any directional move, particularly if we break below the 6810 wall cluster or above 6830. Watch 6810 as the key inflection - a break below triggers cascading dealer buying into the thick negative gamma walls at 6800/6805, while a sustained move above 6830 removes the primary resistance and opens room for momentum continuation.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect wild swings between 6810-6830 until one level breaks decisively.",
